            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-4">China is the ideal stopover for your travel itinerary. As a country known to have the highest population density in the world, many ethnic groups create diversity in culture, customs and traditions... with charming, poetic landscapes. China travel experience handbook will show you practical experiences for your journey to this vast country.</p>
            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Prepare</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">
                Passport: valid for 6 months or more, original passport with blank pages and 01 photocopy of information page with photo.
                Visa declaration form with 4×6 cm card photo: “Visa declaration form for the People's Republic of China” (V2013) with a card photo taken within the last 6 months pasted on the declaration form. Submit the remaining card photo along with other necessary documents
                Original and photocopy of documents proving legal stay or residence, work, or study in Vietnam (for foreign nationals). Photocopy of ID card, original household registration book (for people with Vietnamese nationality)
                Other documents related to the trip (not required but the review agency staff may request additional documents to increase authenticity) such as confirmation of round-trip air ticket reservations and hotel reservations; or a Chinese invitation letter from a Chinese partner (for a business visa), this invitation letter must include details such as
                Personal information of the invited person: full name, gender, date of birth, passport number...;
                Schedule information of the invited person: arrival and departure dates, travel locations...;
                Information of the partner sending the invitation: name of unit, phone number, address, seal, legal representative or signature of the person sending the invitation...
            </p>
